The paper deals with X-codes, which are linear maps used for data compression and error correction. This falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also uses probabilistic combinatorics to give a lower bound, which suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The algorithmic aspect of the paper suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper deals with parity-check matrices for linear codes, which falls under the category of coding theory (cs.CC).
